name: Kepler-165
scenarioDescription:
The Kepler-165 Exoplanetary System

Kepler-165 is a star with 0.665 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.77 times its radius. It is located 1859.32 light years away from the solar system.

Kepler-165 is known to have 2 exoplanets in orbit around it.

Kepler-165 b

Kepler-165 b was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.07 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 8.18 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-165.

The mass of Kepler-165 b is 7.25 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-165 b is 2.32 that of Earth. At 7.25 Earth masses, Kepler-165 b is a so called Super Earth. Super Earths could be terrestrial worlds like Earth, but they could also be ocean worlds or terrestrial worlds wrapped in a substantial atmosphere, in which case some refer to them as Mini Neptunes. No Super Earths are known to exist in our solar system, but if it exists, the so-called Planet Nine could very well be a super Earth, as it is hypothesized to have a mass between five and ten Earth masses.

Kepler-165 c

Kepler-165 c was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its discovery was announced in 2014-03. Its semi-major axis is 0.11 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. It takes 15.31 Earth days to complete an orbit around its host star, Kepler-165.

The mass of Kepler-165 c is 6.60 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-165 c is 2.23 that of Earth. At 6.60 Earth masses, Kepler-165 c is a so called Super Earth. Super Earths could be terrestrial worlds like Earth, but they could also be ocean worlds or terrestrial worlds wrapped in a substantial atmosphere, in which case some refer to them as Mini Neptunes. No Super Earths are known to exist in our solar system, but if it exists, the so-called Planet Nine could very well be a super Earth, as it is hypothesized to have a mass between five and ten Earth masses.
